Now, with Azimuth, I annotate the cells. I will use the Azimuth package to annotate the cells in the filtered Seurat object. The Azimuth package provides a reference-based cell type annotation method for single-cell RNA-seq data.

# If you haven't run SCTransform yet, do it first
obj1205_sct <- SCTransform(obj1205_filtered)


# The RunAzimuth function can take a Seurat object as input
az1205 <- RunAzimuth(obj1205_filtered, reference = "humancortexref")
# Plot the UMAP with Azimuth annotations
DimPlot(az1205, group.by = "", label = TRUE) +
  ggtitle("Azimuth Cell Type Annotations") +
  theme_minimal()
azl1 <- DimPlot(az1205, group.by = "predicted.cluster", label = TRUE, label.size = 3) 
azl1
az1205[[]]
#celltypist -> python
#zellconvertor seruat to scipy which is a bioconductor package.
# Identify highly variable features (genes)
# the 2,000 most variable genes were selected (selection method, vst) and scaled (mean = 0 and variance = 1 for each gene)
d801205_hvgs <- FindVariableFeatures(d801205_normal, selection.method = "vst", nfeatures = 2000)
# Identify the 10 most highly variable genes
top10 <- head(VariableFeatures(obj1205_hvgs), 10)
# Scale the data
# The data was scaled to a mean of 0 and variance of 1 for each gene
obj1205_scaled <- ScaleData(obj1205_hvgs, features = rownames(obj1205_hvgs))
# Perform PCA
#The top 15 principal components were used for clustering (resolution of 0.5), using the FindNeighbors and FindClusters functions
obj1205_pca <- RunPCA(obj1205_scaled, features = VariableFeatures(object = obj1205_scaled))

# Find neighbors
obj1205_neighbors <- FindNeighbors(obj1205_pca, dims = 1:15)
# Find clusters
obj1205_clusters <- FindClusters(obj1205_neighbors, resolution = 0.5)
# Run UMAP
obj1205_umap <- RunUMAP(obj1205_clusters, dims = 1:10)

DimPlot(obj1205_umap, reduction = "umap")
# find markers for every cluster compared to all remaining cells, report only the positive
# ones
obj1205.markers <- FindAllMarkers(obj1205_umap, only.pos = TRUE)
# Filter markers based on avg_log2FC > 1
obj1205.markers %>%
    group_by(cluster) %>%
    dplyr::filter(avg_log2FC > 1)
#Top 10 marker genes of cluster 0
obj1205.markers %>%
    group_by(cluster) %>%
